oman didn't move to the U.S., then try to turn OUR country into HERS. (And now she doesn't have to wear a rag on her head.)", "last_comment_created": 1773343026979, "content": "", "score_down": 1, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 33, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 237, "created": 1773248400000, "id": "2031777168900968464", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2031777116220747776/img/vtDRFGBHz4z_b8dY.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2031777116220747776/pl/vDxlfKpE0Xnjat7E.m3u8?v=dc3", "aspectRatio": [9, 16], "heightRatio": 177, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2031777116220747776/vid/avc1/320x568/rB39wFxtqD9ponEB.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1677756031324102659/QmkoTNg5_normal.jpg", "displayName": "American AF \ud83c\uddfa\ud83c\uddf8", "username": "iAnonPatriot"}, "content": "Why did you move to America? \n\n\u201cBecause I can say Sharia law is retarded without being arrested \u2014 and if someone comes after me I can defend myself.\u201d \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 18982}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASGEG2Vpp", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 72, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8483599, "raw_content": "President Trump is a numbers guy. I get it. He is focused on economic numbers, job numbers, inflation, etc.\n\nWe frequently see positive press releases from the White House announcing deals with foreign companies that have committed to moving manufacturing or making significant investment on shore. As a part of his press releases, he commonly notes how many jobs will be created.\n\nProblem is, many of these \"American jobs\" are not going to Americans and this is still kept under the radar.\n\nWe also see onshore companies and institutions (like Microsoft) firing thousands of American workers only to turn around and apply for thousands of H1Bs. We even see colleges posting jobs to hire H1Bs (as though their own American graduates are not good enough for those jobs)!\n\nI know Trumps people monitor this board, so my question:  When will the president address the H1B problem? I'm not talking about offshoring (that is a different topic of great concern), I'm talking about companies importing super cheap labor by the hundreds of thousands and slotting them into jobs that should go to American citizens.\n\nThis is a HUGE problem. It needs to be addressed as soon as possible!", "author": "Chad_Prime", "created": 1773326806796, "profile_picture": "D3JWYzUFOPX8", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "snakeoil", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "When will President Trump Address the H1B Nightmare?", "last_comment_created": 1773334891838, "content": "<p>President Trump is a numbers guy. I get it. He is focused on economic numbers, job numbers, inflation, etc.</p>\n<p>We frequently see positive press releases from the White House announcing deals with foreign companies that have committed to moving manufacturing or making significant investment on shore. As a part of his press releases, he commonly notes how many jobs will be created.</p>\n<p>Problem is, many of these &quot;American jobs&quot; are not going to Americans and this is still kept under the radar.</p>\n<p>We also see onshore companies and institutions (like Microsoft) firing thousands of American workers only to turn around and apply for thousands of H1Bs. We even see colleges posting jobs to hire H1Bs (as though their own American graduates are not good enough for those jobs)!</p>\n<p>I know Trumps people monitor this board, so my question:  When will the president address the H1B problem? I'm not talking about offshoring (that is a different topic of great concern), I'm talking about companies importing super cheap labor by the hundreds of thousands and slotting them into jobs that should go to American citizens.</p>\n<p>This is a HUGE problem. It needs to be addressed as soon as possible!</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 12, "score_up": 72, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2032085201950842932", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASGEHA54i", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 26, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8484278, "raw_content": "", "author": "blue5707", "created": 1773347093592, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "SavingPrivateGrace", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASGEHA54i.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/DataRepublican/status/2032085201950842932?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "SNAP Shock: Far many more millions in SNAP spent on KING CRAB, LOBSTER & STEAKS  than the Department of War.\n$6.58 billion SPENT ON THESE ITEMS. ", "last_comment_created": 17733